texts.text: Lindsay!
My apologies, Enlightened One...
Everyone, please begin her treatment right away.
I hear Lindsay's condition has stabilized. She's even awake.
It's my fault.
If only I had acted sooner...
No. What you did was truly laudable.
You saved the lives of countless civilians. And Lindsay's.
[sys user_name], please come with me.
There is something I wish to discuss with you and Lindsay.
Lindsay, how are you feeling?
Forgive me, Enlightened One. I'm truly a good-for-nothing.
For now, let us simply rejoice that you came back alive.
I have undergone treatment. I can return to the front lines—
Lindsay, you mustn't push yourself.
But what about the unit?
Yes, about that—
Will you lead the troops, [sys user_name]?
What!
As you can see, Lindsay cannot yet return to the front lines.
Alas, we are left with very little time.
Enlightened One, wait!
They lack experience! They've fought only once since joining—
Even so, I still intend to ask for their help.
After all, [sys user_name] is likely this world's...
Is that clear, Lindsay?

As... As you wish...
Enlightened One.

[sys user_name]...
Can I ask you to lead them?
I understand.
I don't think I can.
You'd better prove you're not all talk. You got it?
Thank you very much. I am truly grateful for your answer.
What, are you afraid?
You've no right to refuse what the Enlightened One requires.
I am loathe to do this, but for the sake of the Brotherhood of—
No, the world. As the Enlightened One, I order you to lead.
There you have it.
While I am on the mend, [sys user_name] will lead the squadron.
Consider their orders mine. You will obey them as you obey me.
Yes, ma'am!
Counting on you, [sys user_name].
You've got more experience in fighting Dx2 than any of us.
We're willing to entrust you with our lives.
Don't get careless. One bad order and people die.
You got that?
>Meanwhile, the Elements had begun their invasion of Tokyo.
Squad 1 reporting capture of the National Diet and ministers.
Squad 2 reporting transfer of power from Kasumigaseki authorities.
Squad 3 reporting command over TV and media stations.
Good, good. Testing Tupsimati is all it took to seize Tokyo.
Demons from the polluted Dragon Stream can cause a bit more havoc
while I take the reins on the world's communication networks.
Then sever the networks, seal off the evil, and hunt down demons.
And then—a peaceful world.
Well, first things first. The Brotherhood of Harmony has to go.
Negative! Can't get ahold of HQ!
What the hell are those things!
Dammit! Dammit!
Never trained for these freaks!
Lost contact with 1st Recon!
They took out the goddamn tank?
Gah!
Tokyo's not safe! We got to go!
How? The trains aren't running, and the car won't even start!
We just have to walk, or else—
Found you.
Eep!
Ah!
This is unreal! Unidentified creatures are swarming Tokyo!
It begs the question: is what we're seeing even of this world?
Hey! That's coming our way!
A-Aah!
Pollution of the Dragon Stream is spreading, as are demons in Tokyo.
We're doing our best to save as many as we can, but—
Know that our fate, humanity's fate, rests on your shoulders.
Here are your orders. I want recon and a report on Tokyo.
Evac as many civilians as you can. Escort them here.
On your order, Acting Commander.
Listen up!
Move out!
Let's go!
Aye!
[sys user_name], please come with me.
Will you lead the troops, [sys user_name]?
After all, [sys user_name] is likely this world's...

[sys user_name]...
Can I ask you to lead them?
